aboutMe:
My name is Hussein Hashish, holds a Bachelor of Laws degree from Ain Shams University, I currently work as a contracts management manager.

I have been captivated by the intricacies of the legal systems and its profound impact on society and this passion driven me to pursue this challenging and rewarding field of study.

During my time at University, I have been fortunate to delve into a diverse range of legal subjects, which has further fueled my curiosity and broadened my perspective, I find particular interest in legal contracts and agreements, as it combines my fascination for law fields and the extent to which the law affects the protection of communities and the rights of individuals.

In addition to my academic pursuits, I have actively sought practical experience to develop my legal personality I have had the privilege of interning at Legal department of Al Tawfekeia for Constructions Co., in addition to other law firms and companies (different specializations and activities) in which I worked during and after completing my academic studies, where I gained hands-on exposure to reviewing and drafting various types contracts and agreements, and raising and following up on legal cases and performing administrative work in courts and governmental bodies, these experiences have not only strengthened my legal knowledge but also honed my research, communication, and constructive thinking skills.

Anticipate and guard against legal risks facing the company.
Ensure proper documentation and undertake vetting of agreements in cases of mergers and acquisitions.
